::DarkMouse::

She looks down wondering how she is going to get around the base if 
she can't walk.  She was feeling so darn useless. She was hoping to 
be up and walking around.  The shaking came back and she just sat 
there on the edge of the table shaking. She wasn't feeling good 
either. but she wasn't going to tell Black Aracnia anything.  She 
owed BA her life. Her debt was a heavy one.
